content: Short simple game. Immersive.

I love reading chats and forum threads, so unveiling a mystery in this format was really fun for me. Along the heart-warming story there is beautiful music, and it truly does feel like you're looking at someone else's phone. As others have said it is short, but very enjoyable, and reminds us all to be our true selves. Definitely recommended for a nice evening read.
This is a really good app when you want to get slightly more insightful about trans experiences and hormones and such- if you take the time to read it-
a must play, i had to look up on the internet the puzzle's answers tho
It was a cute short game. I was half expecting a horror thing with that one lost phone game. But I really like this story
Such a great concept, really well executed. Love this developer's work.

My review keep getting deleted on this game, so I won't give it up, after a few updates, what did they do? I don't care, all I know that my phone won't match the game anymore and that is really inconsiderable of developers. What did they do? They deleted my review times after times. It's not worth the purchase to be honest, the story is not that great either.

Was not worth a purchase. Story is very linear, not very engaging and easily forgettable. Was made to be a "coming out" story where the character runs away from life but the messages, emails, and photos do a poor job of portraying who the main character is. It sort of reminded me of the game "Gone Home" only if Gone Home had a terrible storyline with no twists, turns and 'Ah HA!" moments.

This game is one of the best of the genre (point and click simulation, lol idk what to call it), however none of my achievements are unlocking after completing the game (Android A10E, running latest updates)
The game

I huv not finished this yet but I huv watched youtubers play it I really like it so far but I just want to know if u can replay it after the ending and it does not look like a real phone screen so can u make it look like samsung of IOS please but I still love!
Pretty short, not worth spending money on. The story is not really interesting. But the graphics are pretty cute.
Love the game. Very wholesome, in a weird way.

This game was such an awesome experience! The characters are really well developed & the story resonates so much with me (as someone who identifies with Sam - shhh no spoilers!). It's a fast game, but totally worth it.
I would like there to be a bit more.

This may tackle a tricky subject, but it does not warrant the price, as the game was over almost as soon as it began. The story was alright, yet all the mystery was completely removed by the main character just telling you everything off the bat. The other characters were shallow and stereotypical. The puzzles were just shoved in there to slow you down, they added nothing to the gameplay other than frustration.

Srsly THIS AINT A GAME, BUT MORE LIKE A BOOK! I mean ter isn't even much gameplay @ all. PLS REFUND ME ASAP! THX
Amazing.. been waiting for a game like this

I downloaded this on a whim, thinking it would just be another one of those "Find the missing person" text games, especially after seeing the "Who is Sam" writing on the back of the jacket in the pictures below. In a way, it was, but this one hit much harder than any other game I've played that was even similar to this. I only wish there was another game to continue on with Sam's life.
Really intelligent and üòç lovely
That was a super fun quick puzzle game. LOVE THE MESSAGE! I was totally sucked into the story immediately I forgot it was a game

This game is amazing. The UI of it is very unique and intuitive. The way you learn things slowly through the story is wonderful and by the end I felt very invested in the characters. I got it through play pass for free and had very little expectations, but this game is well worth the little they're charging for it.

Just awesome, I'm astonished, this game is a such complex and interesting masterpiece. It tells such interesting and frightening story. Those 3 bucks were worth it! My recommendation! Only downside it's about 1 hour or so, so just a little time compared to this great experience. I'd appreciated if it were longer but no matter.
The story was interesting and kept me engaged but the game play was overly straight forward and too short.
It is extremely short.I like the soothing BGMs and the colorful pictures. By the way homosexuals,you can change I assure you.

I normally don't rate games, but this one is phenomenal. I was just looking for something to pass the time and instead I discovered the life of someone a lot like me; I was invested immediately, and 100% recommend playing
Can't get past the first hurdle, read the texts from dad, but now what do I do
This game is incredibly charming. It was interesting to see how the story unfolds and the writing is excellent. I also really enjoyed the music in this game.
thank you.
Wow not at all what i expected
I played it all the way through
It. Is. Amazing.
That was a beautiful experience
Good game
It's a fresh and new experience for a mobile game.
A very unique experience!

For what it is, this game is great. I though of this as a lightly interactive visual novel with a very unique interface and concept. As a privacy aware user it felt so utterly wrong to peek into someone elses personal affairs. I will admit that this is way too short for my taste. If you take your time, its about 120 minutes, reading everything. Its awesome writing though. Thanks for exploring this topic. It was a very relatable experience. Thank you for helping me finding my own way with this.
Worst story. The ending that he is just a transwoman. Thats also disgusting and the story is really lame. If i could have a refund, imma ask for it üëéüëéüëéüëé
Cute but short. Don't expect more than a session of game play from this!
Wish there was more gameplay.
A bit too short and a story is quite predictable, but averall nice game
Stupid, useless game.
A really interesting and thought provoking game.
Really touching and sweet!
The game is well-made.

I did not expect this experience. I'm gonna be honest, I always was a person that was neutral when it comes to these kind of subjects. Not really accepting them, because mostly, I couldn't relate. But this...whole experience, opened my eyes. I felt awful at times as I was playing because I was breaking boundaries by going deeper, but it made me understand the struggle of Sam more. It made me more empathic for these kind of things, and I cannot thank you enough.

I really enjoyed the story behind this and found it to be relatable. My only problem was the color scheme. Reading it was harsh on my eyes and gave me a headache. Would be nice if it could have a setting to change that. Despite that though, I played until the end because I found it truly immersive. Thank you for representing the LGBT community on all sides: good, bad, and ugly. Not everyone has terrible experiences or feels the same during the coming out process, so it was wonderful to see.
Incredible game!
Absolutely beautiful.
A very good story about coming out.
Honestly I hated main character in this game... It's example how toxic people can be , ruining other's lives just to stay comfortable.
A short, sweet, enjoyable game. You learn a lot about Samira, and her life. I am proud of her. Good job on the game developers for representation!
Took me about an hour to play. The story truly reveals itself gradually. Impressive storytelling.
Really good game really intruging really hard fun but short

That was such an awesome play! Can't believe it took me this long to buy this game. It was short, sure, but the in-depth story that it provides win over everything else! It has so much character, so much soul in it that I think of it as a reality. Furthermore with what's going on in the world right now, I think this game can open up a new door and opportunity for everyone to just be themselves out there, and not be scared of harsh judgement.
short but cool
I think It would be cool if once you restarted the phone you got "a new person's phone" that way it's not just one story line
This is a beautiful and touching story. I am glad I played it. I am going through this with my child, and this made me feel even closer to them.

I download this game through the play pass, knowing absolutely nothing about it. As I opened the game and began to play, I was immediately drawn in by the uniqueness and layout of the game. It seemed very interesting and we'll put together so I decided to continue playing. The way they piece everything together, the way the game goes about introducing everything and leading everything together. It's so amazing. Words cannot describe just how amazing of a game this is.
Not a bad game. Sometimes it's confusing though with the whole passwords thing.

Just amazing. Absolutely stunning and enjoyable. I read another review saying that the conversations on the dating app were too stereotypical, but honestly I think they were spot on. Overall an awesome game!
This game is amazing and well made im having trouble getting through but i think i will figure it out.

I personally love this game it tells on how certain people without different sexuality think and feel twatrds other's and I would like to say I might not be transgender but i am pansexual/omisexual male so playing a game like this was very fun and informative also I hope Phil and Samira end up together.
Loved it! Quick play through, great concept.
Just a great little puzzle game. Hard to criticize. Story keeps you guessing; an absolute classic.

This game hit me harder than I was expecting. It...I experienced an emotion.playing it that I cannot even describe its genuinely wonderful. I experienced a moment of breaking down into tears, while wave of awful feelings and this sense of excited weightless and happiness at the same time. Breathing became manual during the experience. I don't know how to describe it. Play this game
this is really amazing. great both as an interactive mystery-solving game and as a touching and motivating story
No replayability but great story
Short game, wonderful story.

What a wonderful game! It was immersive and interactive! Well written and the art style is very pretty! It gave me hope!

A great puzzle and a heartfelt story! The game felt very intimate as I explored the phone and peeked into Samira's life! I really enjoyed playing! I hope there are more games like this in the future!

It felt a bit short and the ending was sudden, but it was nice. Even though it didn't take long to complete, there is a lot of information and backstory in the game, and I can appreciate all the work that went into writing it. The characters are relatable and it was fun exploring and finding out new paths to open. Pretty realistic representation of the LGBTQ+ community, with lots of good and accurate info.

Beautiful story. I think I'm half way through but the story has touched me a lot. WARNING ABOUT SPOILERS: This is so well written. Of course the warning at the start did give away a bit of the story but that didn't change much for me. I really empathised with Sam, being a bisexual trans woman who also had a lot of struggles coming out. It really hit home when she had a supportive environment with Phil and Alice. Thank you so much for this game!!
Great.. !!?

it was quite short, that's the only problem I have. its a fun lgbt+ story that I bet can feel close to home. Finished it in about a day of playing though

Super relaxing and wholesome! I love seeing some whoelsome trans rep
Beautiful. When everything clicked I could feel the hope and the freedom, so beautiful!

I cannot discribe this game it's so fantastic!

The game is good with the way you have to figure out what to do with the puzzles and I love the story that it's telling especially the twist that it took! It took some detective work, but it helps with investingating with what happened to Sam.
Such a super cute game!!!

Short but great. It's so good to see myself and my community represented accurately and sensitively in a game.

This is a great wholesome game and I love it! I was immersed on the story from start to finish. I love the game concept of finding a phone and snooping around to get an idea of the previous owner. I felt like I was being able to connect with the character throughout.
This game is really interesting and it has a really good storyline. It's like a book that you have to find clues in to finish. The ending is kinda clever. I loved this game.

I really enjoyed this game, too bad it was quite short! I finished it in about 2.5 hours or so.. playing through the game you really start to feel what Sam felt. You just wanted to keep finding out more and more.

This is one of the best games I've played in a long while. Lived the story! Lived the characters! Lived everything. Finished this in one sitting lol. Thank you for making this and, I'm sure, helping any confused people out there. Be you and be happy!!!!

Fantastic. Must play. Engaging story and characters, clever puzzles, however minus one star because it should be mentioned somewhere the dates are flipped for passwords. I had the correct dates for passwords, but nowhere suggested I should flip them.

content: So I'm in this place of kinda let down but still satisfied with the game, I was expected a sorta simulacra type game, I mean there's the detective work and all and I legitimately got stuck on a couple parts and had to search up the answers for some of the puzzles. Story was alright, this game is more or less a coming out story? Not sure if that's the best way to frame the game but that's what I understood of the game without spoiling much. Tldr: good game overall, id recommend playing it. ¬Ø\_(„ÉÑ)
It good
I couldn't really relate to the story but regardless I loved the gameplay and how much emotion it evoked. It really pulls you in and makes you feel.

I'm not LGBT+, yet oh my god.. This game is so, so eye-opening to the journey so many people go through, and too many of them feel alone. You don't have to be a part of any specific community to specifically relate to this game. It felt like so much of the pain I go through daily isn't just mine, it's the whole world's, yes I probably sound crazy but this game really can make your heart feel that deeply. I never ever empathized with the LGBT+ community so much in my life. I'm so happy I played.
During a long drive, I finished this game, it kept me busy for a couple of hours, and it is NOT a normal phone, this is a very interesting story
Great narrative, and addictive puzzle solving. Love the execution and the ending.

Absolutely loved it, it was very heart warming and I subconsciously picked up on some clues and felt like everything came together when I got to the end. I would have loved to be able to call someone at the end but I still feel like the ending was perfect. This just made my day! I bet I'll play countless more times.
This game was awesome! I spend a lot of time playing games, but this game helped me...I think I learned from this game in spite of myself! Thanks game devs!!

This was ... a really great game. Took me a couple days to really get things started, but when they started, MAN, what a trip. I saved 2 pictures for myself, as a memento. I'm really happy about how it ended

I don't remember how I heard about this game. I didn't know the context but thought the idea was cute. I found it in passing and downloaded it. I wasn't expecting to like this story as much as i did. It hit really close to home. Great Job!

Mad respect for the developers! A very engaging game that completely drew me in. No spoilers, though I do want to commend them for their background knowledge and respectful handling of the storyline. This game is a refreshing change from the status quo.
Wow, that was kinda heavy.
Fantastic game and a fantastic idea. Great premise and very engaging. Something I relate to quite a bit, but a good gateway for anyone who isnt a part of this community
Wonderful

This was a really cool story. I don't want to give any spoilers, but I definitely encourage people to play this. It's short, but really well done and pretty real.

Really fun, makes you think to complete the actions necessary to move forward which is one thing I really like in a game. This game shows strong support for the LGBT community and the struggles the teens go through which everyone needs to learn about even those of us active in that community. We all need to be reminded sometimes. Great game.

Went in to this not knowing what to expect, but wow. I love it. Definitely be aware for the small triggers of homophobia and the like, but the message in this is amazing. Truly a great game with a satisfying conclusion.
Really liked the story behing it would highly recommend
This was beautiful.
That was quite the ride and I was into it for every second I played!

I finished this game last night and I legitimately cried. As a trans man, I've lucked out in a lot of ways with supportive family, but there are always people and things that make being who I am miserable. In a lot of ways, this was a very relatable story. I don't want to spoil it too much so I'll leave it at that. But to the devs, thank you!
Delightful and pleasant puzzle game with a really interesting premise. Not quite like anything I've played before!
Loved this game, and the story of it! I was expecting a horror game to sneak up on me, and while some things were horrible, it was wonderful start to finish!
I bought the game after seeing an ad article in the ios play store. It's a cute game that took about 24 hrs to play. wish there were more LGBT games out there.

Very unique and great story once you get over the creeper reading a very personal story. You get very attached to some of the characters and get to see a person's life from their eyes. Reading a person's phone is a very intimate thing to do.

It was a amazing game. It was beautiful the music is amazing and I somewhat knew what kind of game it was but it was also a completely brand new experience I played it all in one sitting and it was amazing design. It didn't feel like they were spoon feeding u how to play and it wasn't impossible to find out u just had to pay attention and think. I suggest this game to everyone.

Short but enjoyable. The "puzzles" require you to think and investigate but aren't particularly difficult. It's a pretty linear story (you don't really have many options as to what you can do), but it's a good one nonetheless. I've played similar games on PC but the mobile format is definitely nice for these.
Good but too short to justify charging

A wonderfully pleasant innovating way of telling a heart filled story of a trans girl coming to terms with herself and the people that accept or hate her for it. Great story, clever little password puzzles, I asked for a bit of help online tho lol
A beautiful game that explores the reality of coming out in an unaccepting town. This game helped me a lot with my own struggles

Is an interesting concept and while it is an important topic, I feel the story was very short. I wonder if the devs couldn't or shouldn't have gone more in depth as to why certain decisions were made. It sometimes felt Sam tried avoiding confrontation by simply pushing those away who may actually be understanding. It could've been told better imho.
Unique, Fun story.
Great atmosphere and story, but a bit short. Right when I was excited to see what was going to happen it was over
Amazing game, beautifully written.

Its a great story that is very dynamic. Could I personally relate, no not really. But it didn't matter in this game because it really pulled you in. So much emotion, confusion, and anger. By the end I was so proud of Sam! Honestly making notes throughout the game helped me fly through it. I was building a timeline to keep the story straight. But it made it easy to refer back to for the puzzles and codes needed because i already wrote them down. No need to search around and look.
Pretty good game. Great story for everyone including my LGBTQ+ friends. I had to cheat a couple times but that was because I was just being lazy! Play it. Well worth finding someone's phones!
A truly amazing experience. Once I opened the app I couldn't bring myself to close it until I had completed the game.
Had me in the first half until I realized it was about someone discovering who they are by pushing people that cared away. Very poorly executed in story and mechanics.

To die for this game had an amazing story line that warmed my heart loved the gameplay so smooth and I actually felt like this was a lost phone. I couldn't put it down and the puzzles were well constructed and nicely fit with the story line. Well worth the $3.49 and for a girl struggling with my gender (and family) the message at the end struck a tender chord
Incredible story telling!
I never leave reviews. But this game was so well written and beautifully done I HAD to. I absolutely loved it and the characters had depth and the storytelling was so good. I loved it.
I loved it took a lot of thinking
An absolutely wonderful gem. Would recommend
An amazing storytelling game mixed with investigating. Loved it. Looking forward to playing more games like this.
Very interesting game. I really enjoyed it. Would love more like this!
Nice gem of a game. You learn someone's story through their messages and emails to people, very quick and easy to play. Can finish in a few hours or less.

It was fun and sweet. There was a moment where I had no idea what the next step was. There should be a little more prompt to move you from the forum to the diary. I enjoyed the ending and the bittersweet feeling of letting go. There is also a TON of really good information and guidance for poeple dealing with the same issues as Sam in the app. I reccomend reading through the forum thoroughly. Overall, loved it.
Absolutely fantastic. Great narrative, plus it really makes you pay attention to details in order to progress.
Great game, makes me miss my friend who moved to Seattle. Thank you to the developers!

Really awesome game! Took a lot of detective work, but that made it more interesting. I was tempted to look up answers at one point but stayed strong. The game did a very good job of building it's main character piece by piece. It really made me want to keep playing; figuring out one piece of the bigger picture one realization at a time. The phone mechanic is awesome, it makes it way more relatable. Like you are taking a peek into someone's life. I became invested in the story and characters.
Great game! I love it, but developers if your reading this it's really short and you should give it more in later updates. Thank you for creating this game.
It was really boring honestly.

Love this so much. Brain teaser, mystery, LGBT+ all in one! üíúüíúüíúüíú Just sad I finished it so quickly. Maybe an hour and a half? Not saying it's easy or anything so it could occupy others time longer, I'm not sure. Still super awesome just for the messages within.
Short, complicated, but worth every bit of the struggle. A wonderful story about someone finding themselves.
I really enjoy the game. But for some reason, when I scroll through, it really hurts my eyes. I asked a few other people just be sure and they have the same response.
Amazing!

An entertaining and emotional narrative. Though the subject matter isn't significant to me personally, I felt it was tastefully and respectfully delivered, and used organically in the games puzzles. The detective work was a bit exciting and fulfilling to complete too.
Unique game. Wholesome experience.
Amazing

This game is extremely immersive and very very easy to get hooked on, me and my girlfriend stayed up for 2 days searching the phone and its contents only to be amazed by what we found. I highly recommend this game!!
Short and sweet! I loved the graphics!
Meh. It was ok. Not bad, not great. I enjoyed it but it wasn't phenomenal.

Simply an amazing game. I identify with the main character a lot. This was a surprise, as I only downloaded the game bc of Google Play recommending it. Great job to the devs: keep it up!

Really interesting and unique game! I wish it was longer though.

I want to write everything, but 500 characters is so limiting... First of all, AMAZING game, very informative. It's not something I would have normally played, but my wife suggested it to me, and I'm glad she did. (Mild spoiler:) I've been struggling with my gender identity, and after consulting my therapist who seemed incredibly uncomfortable, I got really depressed. Thanks to this game, I'm feeling a little better and I'm joining a Transgender club at my local LGBTQ center! Thank you so much.

Phenomenal, perfect, best in its class. Truly the best meta game on this whole damn store. I really wish I didn't relate as hard as I did this game. But also, I really, really do. Fantastic investigation gameplay, perfectly written characters, and an ending that I could only respond to by putting my phone down, and smiling. This is a work of art, and deserved every bit of praise possible. Thank you, truly, for making this game.

Lost phone games live and die by their writing. I haven't seen writing this ham-fisted and obvious since Crash. If you can't tell the entire message of the game by the end of the first text conversation, try reading it again. Some conversations read like cliche high school PSAs about consent, LGBT people, etc. Every guy on the dating app is only interested in looks - except the magical gay of course! Being bi myself I could only roll my eyes at the lack of any subtlety whatsoever. It's so bad!

You'll wish you could talk to them. Play this game.

As a transgender person myself, I was stunned at how much I could truly 
relate to the game. I haven't found a game like this in a while. It was a 
rather quick game, but it didn't deter from the purpose behind it. And then 
to have that final email between Alice and Sam while you've finished 
reading the diary, it catches you off guard. I'm not sure if there were any 
others who did this, but I was curious to know what would happen if I sent 
the draft email that Sam had been writing to Alice, so I did. And I don't 
know if I'm overthinking it or not, but I think that was also a test to see 
how a person limits themselves to someone else's device. All in all, a 
great game. And I think it could be open to more games like this, with 
maybe more of a storyline.

Fairly decent game. Controls weren't terribly designed, however I felt I 
had to really press on the screen to get the controls to work. To be fair 
though I am in android P beta. Other than that, art is nice, very phone 
like. Neat puzzles for getting through passwords, have to get creative. The 
writing though... Not great. It seems like they are trying to educate the 
audience. Which is fine, however I feel the people playing this game, 
already know alot about this kind of thing. So it's more spoon feeding 
facts and scrapping by it as "fluff". As someone on the outside looking in, 
the diary was awesome, but lacked details I think. Parts of it were rushed, 
and I wasn't able to get a handle on the true feelings of the friends in 
the scenario. I would love to see more uninformed, and confused friends, 
who have never thought about Sam in this light. Supportive or unsupportive. 
I found there was only homophobic people or supportive people. No one on 
the edge of uncertainty. Over all though, really enjoyed it. Little too 
short for my liking though ;).

So, it's a great game in terms of promoting openmindedness and acceptance, 
if you don't have a problem with taking a morally gray (at best) standpoint 
regarding privacy (I didn't :P The major thing is, though, this is an 
incredibly short game. Like, I didn't time myself but it MAY have taken 2 
hours. And there are no multiple endings, there's no way to get more 
content going back because by default you have to go through it all to 
complete the story. So absolutely no replay value there. Considering 
everything, I'd say in terms of app prices these days, when you can buy 
full, practically endless apps for 99 cents, I'd say this app is 
overpriced. It's a good app, but not just not long or complex enough to 
warrant the price. I mean it's an app, so it's only a few dollars, so it's 
not the end of the world like people treat it, but...still. At the end I 
just kinda stared at the screen for a minute or two, waiting for something 
else to happen because, like, is that IT?

Short, underwhelming, and at times sends the wrong message. MAJOR SPOILERS: This game is about trans, gender identity, LGBT communities, etc. etc. etc. Ad nauseum. While this "game" does a terrific job at creating authentic feelings and reactions to someone confused about their identity, it ultimately gives the moral "it's okay to feel this way and sometimes you just have to run away." That's exactly what the character does. They leave. The game creates arguments like "my family is homophobic" (here's exhibit A) But really it just showed me that close-mindedness is not limited to bigotry. To give a big middle finger to everyone and just leave without telling anyone creates a culture that seems to state "embrace cowardice". Run from problems. Even the character's girlfriend attempted suicide when (s)he dumped her and the flimsy excuse of "I tried calling her but she wouldn't talk to me" is BS to me. Did you try email? Letters? Going in person? Nope. Just self-centeredness. Yes, it is difficult. But the message this game sends bothered me. However, trying to create awareness, and more importantly, empathy, is a worthy cause and the concept of sleuthing through a random phone was refreshing and entertaining despite finishing it in 2 hours (including reading everything... even deleted emails). Try other games that tell outstanding stories, are trying to raise awareness, and are similarly priced like What Remains of Edith Finch and Gone Home.

Yes, there's no replay value but it's 3 bucks and gives you a couple hours if you really dive in and immerse yourself. No one complains about the replay value of movies or books. Obviously, this is a reading heavy puzzley game, with a heavy emphasis on character. One puzzle near the end is a little obtuse, theres an info dump section of which only a small bit is required, but it may feel like a slog for obsessives, and the credits scroll really weird and jittery.  That's how good this game is - I'm nitpicking over the CREDITS. Play it, love it, support mobile games that offer focused, one off experiences, instead of addicting Skinner box grind farms.

I hope it reaches a lot of people this way and I hope it makes a lot of people think.  Game play is good and smooth, I found the graphics in you're second game better these annoyed me. Tekst is well written and keeps me wanting to find what happens to the main character. So end result is 5 out of 5 stars and I'm looking forward to the next game.

As an entry into whay seems to be an emerging genre of "found phone" games, this ended up being really emotionally touching. While I was initially a little put off by the painted aesthetic, I still found myself repeatedly using my actual phone's controls rather than the game's. Scrolling in this game feels a little weird, though.  The payoff at the end was extremely worth it, though. Without spilling anything, I have to say that the final moments of this game I was legitimately worried and stressed out over the possible fate of the "original owner". The tension was magnificent, and the payoff when you learn that fate is so worth it.  A lovely game that I'm glad I played, and I'll likely play the sequel the next time I have a long weekend.

Some people have stated that they finished it in 10 minutes, but if you read through everything (like I did) and try to figure out the passwords yourself, I'd say it would take about 2 hours. Whilst that isn't a lot of time, for only a couple of quid, I don't mind it. For a similar price, I can get a 2 hour long Doctor Who audio story from Big Finish (if I buy one of the early releases, but it's a lot more for the recent ones that I also listen to), so to me, this game is good value for money. I hope you're able to enjoy the experience of this game. As you may have noticed, I haven't said what the game is about because I feel you need to find out for yourself. Have fun.

content: One of the best indie games I've played, good story and plot, the concept is awesome, and even the soundtrack is great! It's seriously a great game!

A Normal Lost Phone is a masterpiece. Whoah. The writing style perfectly fits with the thematic of the game : never too caricatural, but always realistic and visceral. And the way the game makes you progress through the phond and, then, through the identity of Sam is mere genius. The fourth wall (i don't know if this expression does exist in english ?) is sometimes broken, but the major part of the genius of A Normal Lost Phone resides in the way it makes you feel which things don't make sense in society. It puts you just ahead of your own way to see what is depicted in the game, and tells you : "You see, even you has not seen everything that was wrong before I put it just under yout nose". Little by little, parts of what seemed normal to you retroactively change in your mind and become terrific, as their true signification is revealed more and more. And this is the best way to make you realize that there are a lot of things that are wrong in the whole society. Beautiful.
Very clever idea and very well implemented. Well done

I was really into it when I was stuck in a car on a road trip but didn't finish it then because I got stuck. I then came back to it a few days later and remembered what it was I was supposed to do but still got stuck. This brings up the one main problem I had with it. If you're stuck and just don't know what to do after a while of trying, you may be tempted to look up what to do. I did this with a website that luckily just gave a few hints to the puzzle before just telling you the solution. Although, at times some of the solutions made me think that I never would've figured it out without the guide. This is a problem because being stuck doesn't do you any good but looking up the solution really took the joy out of the puzzle you're trying to solve, and because there aren't that many puzzles it's a sizeable chunk forfitted every time you do it.

I find myself conflicted. On one hand, A Normal Lost Phone is an important work in the vein of Gone Home that sheds light on an experience too often ignored in media. On the other, the game suffers to convince me that the people I become involved in are real. The text feels too formal, the gameplay too linear, the environmental detail too sparse. The overall effect is that the game felt more educational than empathetic (which can be admirable in its own right but is awkward here). While I still think this is a must play for anyone with a phone, I wish it were so much more.

That is impossible for a game like this. Do you think the people who put time money and resources into making this game should just give it away for free? Pretty boring
Overall fantastic! A little obtuse, but the "story" really sucks you in. And the plot twist is fantastic. Great play, and definitely worth $3!

(SPOILER ALERT) I love the idea of going through a phone, collecting details and passwords from different aspects of someone's life, but it felt a bit short to me. Also, I was fairly disappointed that the whole plot was that he was trans and trying to deal with it. I was honestly expecting a better story,  better climax, it felt a bit too much like a persuasive argument for trans acceptance rather than a game.
The game is too short for the price.

Love the story of this interactive experience! However the final words were a little on the nose and could have implied your final action more instead of spelling it out for us. Overall very good but would have enjoyed more QnA in the forum
Amazing story and idea

Pretty cool little investigation game with an interesting story. Short and sweet, maybe a bit simple but really enjoyed it. Great characters who are portrayed cleverly through text (e.g  the dad who always signs his text messages, or the uncle who uses "..." way too much were really reminiscent of real life for me!) Could relate a lot to main character and was compelling to peek into someone's life this way.
There should be more games like this. True to the medium and its Storytelling capabilities.
Its totally not worth the 3‚Ç¨  Its a game you can finish in 14 minutes
A well-written and important game.

The mystery and how you unravel said mystery is great. Ethically speaking, you are going through someone's phone, accounts, etc. Which makes you feel like a creep. The overall conclusion and story though leaves me rolling my eyes a bit. Maybe it's because I've played one too many LGBT games and seen one too many reveals in shows recently. I've never played a game that represented the trans community so well. I'm in shock at how well this was done. What a cool game! I'm a trans woman, and this game brought the FEELS in a BIG way. Thank you for making this.

It was OK, but nothing groundbreaking. It's a shame that you're not really given much choice in how to proceed. You're sort of railroaded into doing the right thing. Which is annoying. I do have to agree with others in that the story was not what I was expecting. But it was a pretty cool experience nonetheless.

The game is ambiguous. One side it is unusual, very realistic and sometimes funny. You can even imagine this kind of situation in the real life. But on the other hand the game gives food for thought about serious questions which are very hot in some countries.
Nice concise story-based point and click.

I was expecting some kind of real mystery, like the description suggested, not this LGBT stuff. Don't get me wrong, the game, as a concept is great, but I'm having rather mixed feelings about it. Some of the posts on the forums were really dumb, like, I'm not offended, but I strongly disagree with them...  It would have been great if we got to choose in the end whether to tell/text his dad about his secret or not. I'd feel slightly more satisfied if I told him about his son. Yes I'm mean.

Good story, but overall it feels too derivative of the game 'Gone Home' just in a cell phone instead of a house. I mean, both even involve (SPOILER ALERT) an LGBT youth named Sam running away from home (END SPOILER). It feels like they wanted to make Gone Home but Gone Home already existed so they went 'okay how can we make it different'.

Excellent. The intimacy overwhelms you and makes you question your own reasons for continuing to dig. It's excellent story and excellent execution. Sorry to see Kotaku is on the wrong side of this one. Get it.
It was an intriguing and well-written LGBT-oriented game, but I finished it in less than 30 minutes.

Nice idea, but sometimes it's pretty obvious that it's designed to be linear. You only get the next clue once you found the current one. Also some of the texts feel like they were taken from an edutainment game and not like they were written by people chatting one the internet.

There were many moments in this game that hit close to home for me. I found myself tearing up with real empathy for the phone's owner. A normal lost phone tells a much too real story about love, relationships, and being yourself and I really admire that.    These are the mobile games that I really enjoy and that I crave.
so original and good, waiting for the second installment! pls make another story involving alien abduction etc etc scifi theme, good job devs!
Not short at all it was the perfect length, took me a while to figure some passwords but over all amazing! Worth it
Reminded me a lot of Gone Home. A fun little game which I'd recommend to anyone with the patience to read.
great game! I'm very nosy, so I love the idea here of just snooping through somebody's life and putting the pieces together. Story was compelling and I even learned something new.
Really great little game, albeit quite short. Still worth it.

Very well done puzzle game. It wasn't so long that I got bored, but it was long enough for me to feel like I got my money's worth. The passwords are all guessable, and I didn't have to go to a walkthrough.
Only installed 5 minutes ago but already hooked!
Good story very engaging however it felt rather short
Great story. Thought I knew what was going to happen but was surprised.
Wow. Started this and couldn't stop playing until I finished. Such a great narrative. I loved this game.
Wow. This is a fantastically done little game, and I hope more will come of this in the future.

A Normal Lost Phone is an excellent entry in what seems to be a burgeoning trend of non-linear interactive storytelling in indie games. It consistently gives the player ample reason to dig deeper into the narrative, and though I'm sure I could have finished the game without scouring every bit of text provided, the strength of the narrative compelled me to do so anyway. Given that it's a mystery game, there's not much I can say about the game's plot other than that it's quite timely and well-wrought, a story that needed badly to be told. One potential quibble is the sheer volume of text that explicitly serves the game's thematic core, but it's handled well and isn't essential to completing the game. I look forward to seeing more from this developer in the future.
